---
title: Shawarma-Spiced Beef & Golden Raisin Pitas with Pickled Onion & Lemony White Sauce
description: Pita pockets: making portable food possible since...the beginning of recorded culinary history?! Our chefs ditched the ole cave fire for a stove and swapped the spit-roasted game for savory shawarma-spiced beef sautéed with plump golden raisins. It’s all tucked into a fluffy, warm pita pocket layered with quick-pickled red onion and a tangy lemon cream sauce. With a side of crunchy blue corn chips for swiping up any tasty loose ends, you’re good to go (or stay)—no hunting and gathering required!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/shawarma-spiced-beef-golden-raisin-pitas-926fb632.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/646466a398366a49c9018783.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shawarma-spiced-beef-and-golden-raisin-pitas-646466a398366a49c9018783
author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Middle East
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 890 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 75 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 790 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1%unit}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced)

Quarter @lemon{1%unit}(quartered).

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the lemon, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until softened, ~{30-40%seconds}. Uncover and stir, then set aside to pickle.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @ketchup{1%unit}, @golden raisins{1%oz}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, a big pinch of salt, and @pepper{pinch}.

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Meanwhile, wrap @whole wheat pitas{2%unit} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-40%seconds}. Halve pitas; gently pull apart to create pockets.

> TIP: Halve pitas one at a time to make opening easier and prevent sticking.

In a second #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and juice from one lemon wedge. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Fill pita halves with beef. Top with white sauce, pickled onion (draining first), and as much @?hot sauce{1%tsp} as you like.

Divide pitas between plates. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.